CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 5, 1955, pg. 6 reads: "District Attorneys Confer - District Attorney Alfred Harris of Hill City Youth Municipality (seated on left) gathers information on effective law enforcement from District Attorney James F. Malone Jr., of Allegheny County, at a conference in Mr. Malone's office Tuesday morning. Standing are, left to right, Carl Redwood and Howard McKinney, assistant director and director, respectively, of the Hill District Youth government, which has been applauded for its effective program in reducing juvenile delinquency. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Hill City "District Attorney" Alfred Harris, and Allegheny County District Attorney James F. Malone Jr. seated, with Carl Redwood and Howard McKinney standing behind them for meeting in Malone's office
